&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About This Role&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced Associate Director of Nursing to join our team. In partnership with the rest of the Oak Brook Leadership Team, you will play a key role in building and shaping a strong culture at the location, while offering direct coaching and development to our team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our state-of-the-art facility in Oak Brook is modern, bright, and creates an inviting therapeutic space for both patients and employees alike.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What&amp;nbsp;You’ll&amp;nbsp;Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In partnership with the COO, assumes authority, responsibility, and accountability for the delivery of nursing services at the facility&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the various activities of this department and to ensure that proper and&amp;nbsp;timely&amp;nbsp;healthcare is provided to our patients&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and implement nursing policies and procedures that conform to current standards of nursing practice, facility philosophy, and operational policies while maintaining compliance with state and federal laws and regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate and interpret policies and procedures to nursing staff, and monitor staff practices and implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee personnel selection, supervision practices, and ongoing training and evaluation for the nursing department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct staff nurse evaluations and training regarding clinical practices, EMR use, and Compass Health Center protocols&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with staff nurses and treatment team to develop, support and coordinate services that ensure delivery of holistic and individualized quality care to Compass Health Center patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote customer service and hospitality and responds to and adequately resolves complaints or concerns from patients and their families about nursing services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assure staff is trained in fire and disaster and other emergency procedures, and evaluates performance during drills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exercise overall related administrative functions and clinical responsibilities within the scope of nursing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aptitude to gain working knowledge and expertise of staff nurse duties and responsibilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as requested&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hold a BSN degree&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Nurse with current licensure to practice in Illinois&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are certified in Healthcare Provider CPR&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of progressive nursing experience, ideally with 1+ years of management experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mental health experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High degree of leadership, excellent interpersonal communication skills, organizational ability, and time management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess excellent therapeutic communication skill&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Frequently required to walk; use hands to finger, handle, or feel; and reach forward with hands and arms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Often required to sit and stoop, kneel, or crouch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The employee must be able to lift and/or move up to 25 pounds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
