&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Weekly outpatient therapy isn&#39;t always enough, and a trip to the ER isn&#39;t the only answer. Patients and their families rely on Compass Health Center when in crisis – every day, we help people overcome depression, anxiety, suicidality, obsessions/compulsions, trauma, chronic pain, and other obstacles in order for our patients to live freely.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About This Role&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;At the core of Compass we believe in the power of community and connection, which is why we are committed to our group-based programming. As a group therapist in our Child and Adolescent Programs, you will spend the majority of your time with our patients facilitating evidenced based groups using modalities like CBT, DBT, and ACT. We are seeking new and experienced clinicians with a passion for delivering dynamic and informative groups for our patients. If you are seeking an opportunity to provide exceptional care, we’d love to have you on our team.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;Our state-of-the-art facility in Oak Brook is modern, bright, and creates an inviting therapeutic space for both patients and employees alike.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Developing and implementing DBT/CBT skill groups, working with patients aged 8-13 (child program) and 14-17 years old (adolescent program)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Providing crisis intervention and staff support, as needed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
